# .claudeignore — tells Claude Code which files to skip when reading the codebase
# Follows .gitignore syntax. Prevents accidental context bloat from large/sensitive files.

# Python runtime artifacts — never useful for code review
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo

# Virtual environments — thousands of library files, none of them yours
**/.venv/
**/venv/

# Bot state — live portfolio data, not source code
**/state/

# Credentials — should never enter context under any circumstance
**/.env
**/*.pem

# Git internals
**/.git/

# Large running logs — too big to be useful, check via /catchup or /status instead
Build Log.md

# Worktrees — stale Claude Code worktree branches
.claude/worktrees/
